BACKGROUND: Intensity modulated radiation therapy (IMRT) is a radiation therapy 
technology that facilitates the delivery of an improved dose distribution with 
less dose to surrounding critical structures. This study estimates the longer 
term effectiveness and cost-effectiveness of IMRT in patients post radical 
prostatectomy.
METHODS: A Markov decision model was developed to calculate the incremental 
quality adjusted life years (QALYs) and costs of IMRT compared with three 
dimensional conformal radiation therapy (3DCRT). Costs were estimated from the 
perspective of the Australian health care system.
